# TokenGuard overview

TokenGuard is a Go reverse proxy / financial firewall for LLM APIs.

- Guarded mode: Turso budgets + usage, Upstash Redis loop breaker, `pricing.json` costs
- Proxy-only: `TOKENGUARD_GUARD_ENABLED=false` (no budget/loop)
- Mgmt/dashboard require guard enabled and `TOKENGUARD_ADMIN_SECRET` (16+ chars)

## Always

- Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/STRUCTURE.md` before large changes
- Keep money as micro-USD integers; never invent model prices in code
- Strip `X-TokenGuard-*` before upstream; pass provider auth through
- Prefer env config (document in `.env.example`) over CLI flags

## Do not

- Enable mgmt without guard wiring
- Store plaintext API keys in the DB
- Soft-fail open on missing Redis/Turso in guarded mode
